The paper focuses on the impact of simulator accuracy on architecture design decisions in the GPGPU space, specifically in the memory system design. This falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.ARCH) and performance analysis (cs.PF). The paper also discusses the need for enhancing the level of detail in architecture simulators as system complexity continues to grow, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY).
